03/01/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova said on Friday (31 December) that while 2004 was a year of progress, 2005 would be a historic one for the province. 
In his New Year's address to the public, Rugova reviewed 2004's achievements, including the tightening of security and elections that resulted in the formation of new institutions. 
He expressed hope that the strengthening of the institutions would continue in 2005 and that implementation of internationally set standards would be successful. 
(Beta, Tanjug, KosovaLive - 31/12/04)
